---
layout: default
---
<div class="home">
    <style scoped>
        body {
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
        }

        .call-out_img {
            background-image: url('{{ site.header_feature_image | relative_url }}');
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            background-size: 100% 90%; /* Adjust as needed */
            background-position: center;
            min-height: 50vh;
            display: flex;
            flex-direction: column;
        }

        .text-box {
            position: relative;
            top: 40px;
            left: 50%;
            transform: translateX(-50%);
            width: 700px;
            padding: 10px;
            background-color: #f0f0f0;
            border: 0px solid #ddd;
            font-size: 15px;
            color: #2171b5;
            font-family: 'Avenir Next LT Pro';
        }

        .text-box2 {
            position: relative;
            top: -100px;
            left: 40%;
            transform: translateX(-50%);
            width: 400px;
            padding: 10px; /* Add padding to create space between image and border */
            background-color: #f0f0f0;
            border: 2px solid #ddd; /* Add border */
            border-radius: 10px; /* Add border-radius for rounded corners */
            overflow: hidden; /* Ensure the border encloses floated elements */
        }

        .image-container {
            text-align: center; /* Center the image horizontally */
        }

        .image-container img {
            width: 180px;
            height: 150px;
            border-radius: 50%;
            margin-top: -100px; /* Adjust as needed to align the image with text */
            margin-left: -120px; /* Adjust as needed to align the image with text */
        }
    </style>

    <div id="main" class="call-out call-out_img">
        <h1>{{ site.header_text | default: ""}}</h1>
    </div>

    <!-- Text box -->
    <div class="text-box">
        <p>
            As a physicist, I develop mathematical models and utilize computer simulations to study material properties for nanoelectronic applications. In addition to computational work on materials, I have also used optical interferometric microscopy to characterize the surface topography of solar cells and optical flats. Finally, I am proud to highlight my solid foundation in data analytics, using data science, machine learning, and optimization techniques throughout my academic career.
        </p>
    </div>

     <!-- Image box -->
    <div class="text-box2">
        <div class="image-container">
            <img src="assets/img/pexels/amir.jpg" alt="Avatar Image" class="avatar">
        </div>
    </div>

    {% capture _blog %}{% include blog/blog.liquid %}{% endcapture %}
    {{ _blog | split: " " | join: " "}}
</div>
